text:
I have included five different score metrics that could be used for analysis:

Species Score Sum (per 1 km²): Calculated using species presence within each KBA, allowing the total species score to be summarized per KBA.

Number of Species: Included for interest; shows how many species occur in each KBA, but not intended as a primary analysis metric.

Sum KBA Score: The sum of all grid cell scores that intersect with a KBA.

Mean Grid Score: The average score of all grid cells intersecting a KBA.

Area-Corrected KBA Score: Similar to the species score calculation, but the sum of grid scores is divided by the area of the KBA to standardize across KBAs of different sizes.


